cure major sponsorship deals that fund those lucrative salaries?\", \"from\": 625, \"to\": 803, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"more niche sports - sports\", \"from\": 640, \"to\": 666}, {\"ngram\": \"stadiums\", \"from\": 684, \"to\": 692}, {\"ngram\": \"major sponsorship deals\", \"from\": 744, \"to\": 767}, {\"ngram\": \"those lucrative salaries\", \"from\": 778, \"to\": 802}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Athletes who compete in the Olympic Games often dedicate their lives to preparing for competitions, but for the public at large, their sport is only front and centre for a short period every four years.\", \"from\": 805, \"to\": 1007, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Athletes\", \"from\": 805, \"to\": 813}, {\"ngram\": \"the Olympic Games\", \"from\": 829, \"to\": 846}, {\"ngram\": \"their lives\", \"from\": 862, \"to\": 873}, {\"ngram\": \"competitions\", \"from\": 891, \"to\": 903}, {\"ngram\": \"the public\", \"from\": 913, \"to\": 923}, {\"ngram\": \"their sport\", \"from\": 934, \"to\": 945}, {\"ngram\": \"only front\", \"from\": 949, \"to\": 959}, {\"ngram\": \"centre\", \"from\": 964, \"to\": 970}, {\"ngram\": \"a short period\", \"from\": 975, \"to\": 989}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The truth is, many of these athletes - despite their professionalism and commitment - do not even earn a full-time salary from their sport.\", \"from\": 1009, \"to\": 1148, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The truth\", \"from\": 1009, \"to\": 1018}, {\"ngram\": \"these athletes\", \"from\": 1031, \"to\": 1045}, {\"ngram\": \"their professionalism\", \"from\": 1056, \"to\": 1077}, {\"ngram\": \"commitment\", \"from\": 1082, \"to\": 1092}, {\"ngram\": \"a full-time salary\", \"from\": 1112, \"to\": 1130}, {\"ngram\": \"their sport\", \"from\": 1136, \"to\": 1147}]}, {\"sentence\": \"So, how much do athletes get paid for taking part in the Olympics, and where does the money come from?\", \"from\": 1150, \"to\": 1252, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"athletes\", \"from\": 1166, \"to\": 1174}, {\"ngram\": \"part\", \"from\": 1195, \"to\": 1199}, {\"ngram\": \"the Olympics\", \"from\": 1203, \"to\": 1215}, {\"ngram\": \"the money\", \"from\": 1232, \"to\": 1241}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Australian athletes are not paid to compete in the Olympic Games, but they do not have to fund their own participation.\", \"from\": 1254, \"to\": 1373, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1254, \"end\": 1264, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australian_Government\", \"score\": 0.8312510900866823, \"rank\": 0.19339761989619192, \"text\": \"Australian\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australian_Government\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australian_Government\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the Olympic Games\", \"from\": 1301, \"to\": 1318}, {\"ngram\": \"their own participation\", \"from\": 1349, \"to\": 1372}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The Olympics funding model for Australians is complex and varies depending on each athlete and sport, but attendance costs (such as flights, accommodation and food) are often covered by either the Olympic Committee, sponsors, or grants.\", \"from\": 1375, \"to\": 1611, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The Olympics funding model\", \"from\": 1375, \"to\": 1401}, {\"ngram\": \"Australians\", \"from\": 1406, \"to\": 1417}, {\"ngram\": \"each athlete\", \"from\": 1453, \"to\": 1465}, {\"ngram\": \"sport\", \"from\": 1470, \"to\": 1475}, {\"ngram\": \"attendance costs\", \"from\": 1481, \"to\": 1497}, {\"ngram\": \"flights\", \"from\": 1507, \"to\": 1514}, {\"ngram\": \"accommodation\", \"from\": 1516, \"to\": 1529}, {\"ngram\": \"food\", \"from\": 1534, \"to\": 1538}, {\"ngram\": \"either the Olympic Committee\", \"from\": 1561, \"to\": 1589}, {\"ngram\": \"sponsors\", \"from\": 1591, \"to\": 1599}, {\"ngram\": \"grants\", \"from\": 1604, \"to\": 1610}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Jump down to the 'How do Olympic athletes make money?'\", \"from\": 1613, \"to\": 1667, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Olympic athletes\", \"from\": 1638, \"to\": 1654}, {\"ngram\": \"money\", \"from\": 1660, \"to\": 1665}]}, {\"sentence\": \"section of this article to find out more of the financial details.\", \"from\": 1668, \"to\": 1734, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"section\", \"from\": 1668, \"to\": 1675}, {\"ngram\": \"this article\", \"from\": 1679, \"to\": 1691}, {\"ngram\": \"the financial details\", \"from\": 1712, \"to\": 1733}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Ahead of the Paris Olympics,World Athletics announcedit would become the first international federation to award prize money at the Olympic Games.\", \"from\": 1736, \"to\": 1882, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1764, \"end\": 1779, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/World_Athletics\", \"score\": 0.9999999999995453, \"rank\": 6.544265569501348e-13, \"text\": \"World Athletics\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/World_Athletics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/World_Athletics\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the Paris Olympics\", \"from\": 1745, \"to\": 1763}, {\"ngram\": \"the first international federation\", \"from\": 1805, \"to\": 1839}, {\"ngram\": \"prize money\", \"from\": 1849, \"to\": 1860}, {\"ngram\": \"the Olympic Games\", \"from\": 1864, \"to\": 1881}]}, {\"sentence\": \"A total prize pot of $US2.4 million ($3.6 million) has been allocated to reward athletes who win a gold medal in any of the 48 track and field events.\", \"from\": 1884, \"to\": 2034, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"A total prize pot\", \"from\": 1884, \"to\": 1901}, {\"ngram\": \"athletes\", \"from\": 1964, \"to\": 1972}, {\"ngram\": \"a gold medal\", \"from\": 1981, \"to\": 1993}, {\"ngram\": \"the 48 track and field events\", \"from\": 2004, \"to\": 2033}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Apart from that, here's how it generally works.\", \"from\": 2036, \"to\": 2083, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Olympic gold, silver or bronze medals can come with a cash prize, but the amounts vary depending on the event and where an athlete places on the podium.\", \"from\": 2085, \"to\": 2237, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Olympic gold\", \"from\": 2085, \"to\": 2097}, {\"ngram\": \"silver\", \"from\": 2099, \"to\": 2105}, {\"ngram\": \"bronze medals\", \"from\": 2109, \"to\": 2122}, {\"ngram\": \"a cash prize\", \"from\": 2137, \"to\": 2149}, {\"ngram\": \"the amounts\", \"from\": 2155, \"to\": 2166}, {\"ngram\": \"the event\", \"from\": 2185, \"to\": 2194}, {\"ngram\": \"an athlete\", \"from\": 2205, \"to\": 2215}, {\"ngram\": \"the podium\", \"from\": 2226, \"to\": 2236}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It also depends on the country the athletes are representing.\", \"from\": 2239, \"to\": 2300, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the country\", \"from\": 2258, \"to\": 2269}, {\"ngram\": \"the athletes\", \"from\": 2270, \"to\": 2282}]}, {\"sentence\": \"This is because prize money comes from these countries, not the International Olympic Committee (IOC) or the host country.\", \"from\": 2301, \"to\": 2423, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2365, \"end\": 2402, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"International Olympic Committee (IOC)\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"prize money\", \"from\": 2317, \"to\": 2328}, {\"ngram\": \"these countries\", \"from\": 2340, \"to\": 2355}, {\"ngram\": \"the host country\", \"from\": 2406, \"to\": 2422}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Under Australia's Medal Incentive Funding program, individual athletes are paid $20,000 for a gold medal, $15,000 for a silver and $10,000 for a bronze.\", \"from\": 2425, \"to\": 2577, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2431, \"end\": 2440, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia\", \"score\": 0.9998125322127884, \"rank\": 0.00018748069570283363, \"text\": \"Australia\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"individual athletes\", \"from\": 2476, \"to\": 2495}, {\"ngram\": \"a gold medal\", \"from\": 2517, \"to\": 2529}, {\"ngram\": \"a silver\", \"from\": 2543, \"to\": 2551}, {\"ngram\": \"a bronze\", \"from\": 2568, \"to\": 2576}]}, {\"sentence\": \"However, each athlete can only receive one payment - so those who win multiple medals get paid the amount corresponding to their best result.\", \"from\": 2579, \"to\": 2720, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"each athlete\", \"from\": 2588, \"to\": 2600}, {\"ngram\": \"one payment\", \"from\": 2618, \"to\": 2629}, {\"ngram\": \"multiple medals\", \"from\": 2649, \"to\": 2664}, {\"ngram\": \"the amount\", \"from\": 2674, \"to\": 2684}, {\"ngram\": \"their best result\", \"from\": 2702, \"to\": 2719}]}, {\"sentence\": \"For team sports, the payment depends on the size of the team and comes from the Australian Olympic Committee (AOC) rather than the government.\", \"from\": 2722, \"to\": 2864, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2802, \"end\": 2830, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australian_Olympic_Committee\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Australian Olympic Committee\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australian_Olympic_Committee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australian_Olympic_Committee\"}, {\"begin\": 2832, \"end\": 2835, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australian_Olympic_Committee\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.7629334487423078e-17, \"text\": \"AOC\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australian_Olympic_Committee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/res