$250,000\", \"from\": 3088, \"to\": 3097}, {\"ngram\": \"a bronze\", \"from\": 3113, \"to\": 3121}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Under Australia's Medal Incentive Funding program, individual athletes are paid $20,000 for a gold medal, $15,000 for a silver and $10,000 for a bronze.\", \"from\": 3124, \"to\": 3276, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3130, \"end\": 3139, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia\", \"score\": 0.9998125322127884, \"rank\": 0.00018748069570283363, \"text\": \"Australia\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"individual athletes\", \"from\": 3175, \"to\": 3194}, {\"ngram\": \"a gold medal\", \"from\": 3216, \"to\": 3228}, {\"ngram\": \"a silver\", \"from\": 3242, \"to\": 3250}, {\"ngram\": \"a bronze\", \"from\": 3267, \"to\": 3275}]}, {\"sentence\": \"US athletes reportedly receive US$37,500 ($56,259) for a gold medal, US$22,500 ($33,755) for a silver, and US$15,000 ($22,503) for a bronze.\", \"from\": 3280, \"to\": 3420, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3280, \"end\": 3282, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_dollar\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 6.266479371110264e-14, \"text\": \"US\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_dollar\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_dollar\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a gold medal\", \"from\": 3335, \"to\": 3347}, {\"ngram\": \"a silver\", \"from\": 3373, \"to\": 3381}, {\"ngram\": \"a bronze\", \"from\": 3411, \"to\": 3419}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Athletes from some countries - such as Norway, Sweden and the United Kingdom - do not get paid at all for winning medals.\", \"from\": 3422, \"to\": 3543, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3461, \"end\": 3467, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Norway\", \"score\": 0.999531132416319, \"rank\": 0.00044376686531455374, \"text\": \"Norway\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wiki